According to rule number 3,
- The sections between $\mathbf{0}$ and $\mathbf{- 1}$ (for example, point -0.4 ) contain only one pole and no zeroes on the right-hand side. It means that the sum is odd (i.e. 1). So, it exists on the root locus.
- The sections between $\mathbf{- 1}$ and $\mathbf{- 3}$ (for example, point -2.1 ) contain only one pole and one zero on the right-hand side. It means that the sum of poles and zeroes is even (i.e. 2). So, it does not exist on the root locus.
