\section*{5. Range for the second section $\mathbf{C} 2$}

The second section is generally of infinite radius. Here, it is a semi-circle of infinite radius. The range of the second section is from -90 degrees to +90 degrees. It can be obtained by:
$\lim _{R \rightarrow \infty} \operatorname{Re}^{j \theta}$
$\theta=-\frac{\pi}{2}$ to $+\frac{\pi}{2}$

If the transfer function is in the form $\mathrm{G}(\mathrm{s}) \mathrm{H}(\mathrm{s})=\mathrm{K}(1+\mathrm{sT}) / \mathrm{s}(1+\mathrm{sT} 1)(1+\mathrm{sT} 2)$, the term $(1+$ $\mathrm{sT})$ can be assumed as sT.

