N is the number of poles and m is the number of zeroes. The value of n is greater than or equal to $m$.

\section*{6. Range for the second section C 3}

In the third section C 3 , the value of $\boldsymbol{\omega}$ ranges from -infinity to zero. The locus of the third section is just the inverse of the polar plot of $\mathrm{G}(\mathrm{j} \omega) \mathrm{H}(\mathrm{j} \omega)$. We can also say that it is the inverse of the first section. The resulted plot will be the mirror image of the polar with respect to the real axis.

\section*{7. Range for the second section $\mathbf{C 4}$}

The argument of the forth section varies from- 90 degrees to 90 degrees. The Nyquist contour of this section has a semicircle of zero radii. The mapping of the section C 4 is given by the condition:
